import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'], label='CO2 levels')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('CO2')
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 levels over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['CO2'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='CO2 levels')
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['CO2'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('CO2 Levels')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 levels?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['CO2'], vert=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('CO2 Levels')
    ax.set_yticklabels([''])
    ax.axvline(data['CO2'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['CO2'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average CO2 level?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    
    max_co2 = data['CO2'].max()
    max_co2_date = data.loc[data['CO2'] == max_co2, 'Date'].iloc[0]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'], label='CO2 Levels', color='blue')
    plt.axhline(max_co2, linestyle='--', color='red', label=f'Highest CO2: {max_co2:.2f}')
    plt.axvline(max_co2_date, linestyle='--', color='green', label=f'Date: {max_co2_date.strftime("%Y-%m-%d")}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 Levels')
    plt.title('What is the highest CO2 level recorded?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
